        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 24 at 5:07PM CDT by NWS Lake Charles LA</headline>
        <description>At 506 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Longville, or 7 miles east of Singer, moving west at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
De Ridder, Merryville, Singer, Fields, De Quincy, Ragley, Longville,
Bivens, Tulla, and Oretta.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
